FBIS4-57802 "drlat101_m_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 Brazil Amendment Reduces Presidential Term to 4 Years Amendment Reduces Presidential Term to 4 Years PY2505024894 Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO in Portuguese 2342 GMT 24 May 94 PY2505024894 Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO Portuguese BFN [Report by Antonio Marcello and Pamela Nunes] [Excerpt] Brasilia, 24 May (AE) -- The next president of the Republic will be elected for a four-year term and will not be able to seek reelection. The Constituent Congress today approved for the second time a constitutional amendment that reduces the presidential term from five to four years. Of the 357 congressmen in attendance, 323 voted in favor of the amendment, 29 voted against it, and five abstained. The possibility of an incumbent president seeking reelection already had been denied during the first vote taken on the issue. [passage omitted]
